{"title":"About","markdown":{"yaml":{"title":"About","about":{"image-width":"10em","template":"jolla","links":[{"icon":"github","text":"Github","href":"https://github.com/mastoffel"},{"text":"{{< ai google-scholar >}} Google scholar","href":"https://scholar.google.com/citations?user=58uLFHoAAAAJ&hl=en&oi=ao"},{"icon":"linkedin","text":"LinkedIn","href":"https://www.linkedin.com/in/mastoffel/"},{"icon":"envelope","text":"Email","href":"mailto:martin.adam.stoffel@gmail.com"}]}},"containsRefs":false,"markdown":"\n\nHi, I'm Martin. At heart, I'm curious about nature and technology and everything in between. Until recently, I was a researcher at the University of Edinburgh working on evolutionary genetics and biostatistics, and also a [PIBBSS](https://www.pibbss.ai/) fellow exploring risks from future AI systems. Now, I'm a Research Data Scientist in the [Research Engineering Group](https://www.turing.ac.uk/research-engineering) at the [Alan Turing Institute](https://www.turing.ac.uk/), combining my passion for building things and tackling new challenges across disciplines. \n\nOutside of work, I like kettlebells, remote islands, wingspan, 5s football, open water swimming, trying to read Gödel Escher Bach, cold plunges, conversations without time-pressure, pull-ups, Rumo, forests, the Economist, intermittend fasting and northern elephant seals.\n\nAlways happy to chat, so feel free to get in touch.\n\n\n"},"formats":{"html":{"execute":{"fig-width":7,"fig-height":5,"fig-format":"retina","fig-dpi":96,"df-print":"default","error":false,"eval":true,"cache":null,"freeze":false,"echo":true,"output":true,"warning":true,"include":true,"keep-md":false,"keep-ipynb":false,"ipynb":null,"enabled":null,"daemon":null,"daemon-restart":false,"debug":false,"ipynb-filters":[],"engine":"markdown"},"render":{"keep-tex":false,"keep-source":false,"keep-hidden":false,"prefer-html":false,"output-divs":true,"output-ext":"html","fig-align":"default","fig-pos":null,"fig-env":null,"code-fold":"none"